WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.480
the newspaper chase. The time is one o'clock in the morning.

00:09.640 --> 00:11.460
The place is the

00:11.460 --> 00:18.200
rights-filled town art gallery. A window opens and a man comes

00:18.200 --> 00:21.840
in. His name is

00:21.840 --> 00:27.580
Harry Black, and he is a thief. It is dark in the

00:27.580 --> 00:30.360
art gallery, but Harry has a

00:30.360 --> 00:36.980
light. He looks across the room at a painting. There it is,

00:37.740 --> 00:40.160
he says. Harry

00:40.160 --> 00:45.320
moves quickly across the room. He stands and looks at the painting.

00:46.200 --> 00:47.220
A million

00:47.220 --> 00:54.560
dollars for this, he thinks. I don't understand it, but he takes

00:54.560 --> 00:55.380
a knife from

00:55.380 --> 01:02.780
his coat. Then he takes the painting very, very slowly from its

01:02.780 --> 01:05.880
frame. Harry goes

01:05.880 --> 01:10.300
back across the room to the window, but he walks into a

01:10.300 --> 01:13.600
table. There is a beautiful

01:13.600 --> 01:19.460
blue glass vase on the table. It falls on the floor and

01:19.460 --> 01:20.840
breaks into a hundred

01:20.840 --> 01:30.180
pieces. Harry smiles. Is that a million dollar vase, he thinks. It

01:30.180 --> 01:33.020
isn't now. He

01:33.020 --> 01:38.620
runs across the pieces of glass to the window. Harry has a

01:38.620 --> 01:43.580
room in Mrs. Allen's

01:43.580 --> 01:49.060
room, quietly up to his room and closes the door. Mrs. Allen

01:49.060 --> 01:50.100
and her daughter,

01:50.380 --> 01:58.320
Janie, are sleeping. They don't hear him. In his room, Harry takes

01:58.320 --> 01:59.300
the painting from

01:59.300 --> 02:04.120
his bag. He puts it in a newspaper. Then he puts the

02:04.120 --> 02:07.720
newspaper under his bed. In

02:07.720 --> 02:13.280
the morning, Janie Allen is in the kitchen. She's putting old bottles

02:13.280 --> 02:14.280
into a box.

02:15.720 --> 02:23.980
Recycling is important, Janie thinks. On the TV, a reporter is at

02:23.980 --> 02:24.140
the

02:24.140 --> 02:30.560
rightsville art gallery. He is talking about the painting. It's a million

02:30.560 --> 02:31.260
dollar

02:31.260 --> 02:38.600
painting, he is saying. Here's a photo of it. Now the reporter

02:38.600 --> 02:39.880
is talking about the

02:39.880 --> 02:48.380
blue glass vase. It's in a hundred pieces now, he says. Janie

02:48.380 --> 02:49.620
looks at the photo of

02:49.620 --> 02:55.480
the vase. Then she asks her mother. Do you have any old

02:55.480 --> 03:00.140
bottles? No, Mrs. Allen says.

03:01.140 --> 03:06.220
That's all, Janie. But the newspaper recycling truck is coming today.

03:07.580 --> 03:17.520
Of course, Janie says. It's Friday. Harry isn't in his room. He

03:17.520 --> 03:18.480
is talking on his

03:18.480 --> 03:25.220
telephone to a man in Seattle. The man wants the painting, but

03:25.220 --> 03:27.000
Harry isn't happy.

03:28.000 --> 03:41.380
$5,000, Harry says. No, it's a million dollar painting. What? No,

03:42.320 --> 03:45.610
I want 50,000, not

03:45.610 --> 03:58.790
five. What? The painting. Yes, I have it. And it's okay. Janie

03:58.790 --> 03:59.990
is looking for old

03:59.990 --> 04:06.370
newspapers. Early on Friday mornings, she takes them from every room in

04:06.370 --> 04:06.830
the house.

04:07.830 --> 04:16.570
Then, later, the newspaper recycling truck arrives. Janie opens Harry's door and

04:16.570 --> 04:16.790
looks

04:16.790 --> 04:22.810
into his room. She always takes his old newspapers or bottles for

04:22.810 --> 04:27.730
recycling. Ah, she thinks. There's

04:27.730 --> 04:34.390
a newspaper under Harry's bed. Janie puts the old newspapers into a

04:34.390 --> 04:35.890
black recycling box.

04:36.770 --> 04:43.270
She runs from the house and sees the truck. Wait, she says,

04:43.830 --> 04:45.550
and she quickly gives the

04:45.550 --> 04:50.850
box to one of the men. Harry is coming back to the

04:50.850 --> 04:54.770
house. He sees the recycling truck,

04:54.770 --> 05:04.750
and he sees Janie. It's Friday, he says. The newspaper. Oh, no.

05:06.690 --> 05:08.890
Harry chases after the truck.

05:09.870 --> 05:21.050
Wait, wait. He says. Janie watches him. What is he doing? She

05:21.050 --> 05:24.370
thinks. Harry jumps into the

05:24.370 --> 05:31.470
back of the truck. I want my newspaper, he says. Where's my

05:31.470 --> 05:35.290
newspaper? But there are

05:35.290 --> 05:41.130
thousands of newspapers in the truck. Janie walks quickly from the house

05:41.130 --> 05:41.870
to the truck.

05:42.810 --> 05:50.430
Why is your newspaper important, Harry? She asks. It's two days old,

05:50.950 --> 05:53.510
but Harry doesn't hear her.

05:54.290 --> 06:01.490
He is thinking, my million dollar painting. Where is it? The men

06:01.490 --> 06:02.810
from the recycling truck

06:02.810 --> 06:08.490
are watching Harry too. But now Janie is looking at Harry's shoe.

06:10.050 --> 06:12.170
There's some blue glass and

06:12.170 --> 06:24.150
Harry's shoe, Janie thinks. Where? Oh. Suddenly, she remembers the photo of

06:24.150 --> 06:25.570
the blue glass face on

06:25.570 --> 06:30.670
the TV. She looks again at the piece of glass and Harry's

06:30.670 --> 06:42.150
shoe. Is it from the vase in the art

06:42.150 --> 06:47.470
of the recycling truck are angry? We're going now. They are saying.

06:48.170 --> 06:51.290
We're late. But I want my

06:51.290 --> 06:57.730
newspaper, Harry says. In the house, Janie is talking to the police

06:57.730 --> 07:01.330
on the telephone. Maybe I'm wrong,

07:01.330 --> 07:09.130
she is saying. But there's blue glass in his shoe. What? Yes,

07:09.550 --> 07:11.850
he's looking for the newspaper now.

07:13.810 --> 07:20.430
Two policemen arrive quickly. Let's look at your shoe. They say to

07:20.430 --> 07:23.490
Harry. Harry doesn't understand.

07:24.450 --> 07:30.470
What's wrong? He asks. One of the policemen takes the glass from

07:30.470 --> 07:31.150
Harry's shoe.

07:32.450 --> 07:37.010
This is a very expensive piece of glass, he says, from a

07:37.010 --> 07:40.190
very expensive vase. Remember?

07:41.930 --> 07:52.410
Suddenly, Harry understands. Oh, no, he says. Police cars and policemen arrive.

07:53.490 --> 07:58.830
The men look in the truck for the million dollar painting. Later,

07:59.330 --> 08:01.190
they find the right newspaper

08:01.950 --> 08:07.710
and they find the painting. Good work, Janie, one of the policemen

08:07.710 --> 08:11.010
says. And there's a reward.

08:12.410 --> 08:18.550
Maybe I can buy a painting with a reward, Janie says. I

08:18.550 --> 08:19.570
like pictures.

